# SCSS Conventions

## Layout: Flexbox by default

Use `display: flex` as the default. Only reach for CSS Grid when flexbox genuinely cannot solve the layout.

## Units: rem for the box model

`reset.scss` sets `html { font-size: 62.5% }`, so `1rem === 10px`. Use `rem` for `margin`, `padding`, `width`, and `height`. Use `px` only for hairline borders and similar fine details.

```scss
padding: 1.6rem;   // = 16px
width: 100%;
height: 4.8rem;    // = 48px
```

## Breakpoint mixin (no raw media queries)

`grid.scss` is auto-injected via Vite `additionalData`, so `breakpoint()` is globally available — no `@use` needed.

Available breakpoints: `xs` (360px), `sm` (600px), `md` (700px), `mdl` (1000px), `lg` (1200px), `xl` (2000px).

```scss
// correct
.card {
  font-size: 1.4rem;

  @include breakpoint(md) {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
  }
}

// wrong - raw media query
.card {
  @media (min-width: 700px) { ... }
}
```

## Flat selectors

Keep nesting minimal. Only nest for:
- Pseudo-classes / pseudo-elements (`:hover`, `::before`)
- State variants (`&.is-active`)
- Breakpoint mixins (`@include breakpoint(...)`)

Do **not** nest descendant selectors — use a flat BEM-style class on the child instead.

```scss
// correct
.card { display: flex; }
.card-title {
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  &:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
}

// wrong
.card {
  display: flex;
  .card-title { ... }   // descendant nesting
}
```

## Property order

Order properties from broad layout impact to finer details. Maintain this order inside breakpoint mixins as well.

1. **Layout** — `display`, then flex sub-props (`flex-direction`, `flex-wrap`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `align-self`, `gap`), then `position`, `z-index`
2. **Box model** — `margin`, `padding`, `width`, `height`
3. **Visual** — `border`, `color`, `background`, `box-shadow`
4. **Typography** — `font-size`, `font-family`, `text-align`, `text-transform`
5. **Misc** — `transform`, `transition`, `overflow`, `cursor`

```scss
.example {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 1.6rem;
  position: relative;
  z-index: var(--z1);

  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 1.6rem;
  width: 100%;

  border: 1px solid currentColor;
  background: #fff;

  font-size: 1.4rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;

  transition: opacity var(--ease);
  cursor: pointer;
}
```
